-- India cbank grants preliminary bank licenses to IDFC, Bandhan Financial
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Wed Apr 02, 2014 09:03AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 2 (Reuters) - The Reserve Bank of India said on Wednesday it had granted bank licenses to IDFC Ltd <IDFC.NS> and Bandhan Financial Services that would be valid for 18 months and would be subject to the two financial firms fully complying with central bank regulations.

The central bank will also consider the application of India Post, but under a separate process to be carried out in consultation with the government.